Usage: gui_dump_picture [-help] <name>
                        [-format {BMP GIF JPG JPEG PNG PBM PGM PPM XBM XPM}]
                        [-honor_umask] [-window <string>] [-width <integer> -height <integer>]

-help                         # Prints out the command usage
<name>                        # file name of the picture (string, required)
-format {BMP GIF JPG JPEG PNG PBM PGM PPM XBM XPM}
                              # format of the picture, default is PNG (enum, optional)
-height <integer>             # height of the picture
                              # (int, optional, min=100, max=20000)
-honor_umask                  # honor umask to save the pic (bool, optional)
-width <integer>              # width of the picture
                              # (int, optional, min=100, max=20000)
-window <string>              # id of layout window (string, optional)